-- Bush to meet with Detroit executives next week
-- 
-- Wed Mar 21, 2007 3:32pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/21/businesspro-bush-automakers-dc-idUSWBT00670320070321

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - President George W. Bush will meet 
next week with the chief executives from Detroit's largest 
automakers, the White House said on Wednesday. 

  The March 26 meeting with officials of General Motors 
( GM.N ), Ford Motor Co. ( F.N ) and DaimlerChrysler DCX.N will 
focus on alternative fuels, said White House spokesman Tony 
Fratto.